cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with learning optimal control policies in systems where action space is defined by sentences in natural language. This falls under the scope of natural language processing, which is a subfield of CS.CL.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with reinforcement learning techniques to jointly learn text representations and control policies. This falls under the scope of AI, which is a subfield of CS.AI.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper deals with learning optimal control policies using reinforcement learning techniques. This falls under the scope of machine learning, which is a subfield of CS.LG.
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper presents an open-source library for universal access to different text games. This falls under the scope of software engineering, which is a subfield of CS.SD.
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the potential real-world applications of learning optimal control policies in systems where action space is defined by sentences in natural language. This falls under the scope of the societal impact of computing, which is a subfield of CS.CY.
